  "text": "The next result on group model lower bounds was due to Fredman and Saks [CITATION_1] , who introduced the celebrated chronogram technique. Using this technique, they again proved lower bounds for the partial sums problem, stating that any dynamic data structure must have an average cost per operation of Ω(lg n/ lg lg n) over a sequence of n queries and n updates [CITATION_2] . While the lower bound is weaker than the earlier lower bound of Fredman, it holds also for weakly oblivious data structures.",
